6
00:00:21.707 --> 00:00:24.871
business versions of Windows at that time and Windows 95,

7
00:00:24.871 --> 00:00:26.938
Windows 98 were the consumer versions,

8
00:00:26.938 --> 00:00:29.499
in order to install those operating systems,

9
00:00:29.499 --> 00:00:32.855
you normally had one to three floppy disks.

10
00:00:32.855 --> 00:00:34.012
Anybody remember those?

11
00:00:34.012 --> 00:00:38.421
And this was because it wasn't assumed that everybody had a

12
00:00:38.421 --> 00:00:43.224
current generation optical drive or CD drive at that time or DVD

13
00:00:43.224 --> 00:00:45.158
drive a bit later on their computer.

14
00:00:45.158 --> 00:00:47.887
So you would start the computer using old school floppies,

15
00:00:47.887 --> 00:00:52.111
and those floppies don't hold much data so you had a text-based interface

16
00:00:52.111 --> 00:00:55.718
like you see here where you use the keyboard to navigate.

17
00:00:55.718 --> 00:00:57.238
It bootstraps the operating system,

18
00:00:57.238 --> 00:01:00.068
it gives you the opportunity to load some device

19
